========================================
Required tools
========================================

- SUN Java SDK 1.6: http://java.sun.com/javase/downloads/index.jsp
- Eclipse 3.4+: http://www.eclipse.org/downloads/
- MSysGit 1.6: http://code.google.com/p/msysgit/

========================================
Initial development environment setup
========================================

** Note: all names between < and > are meant to be replaced by the corresponding information.

1. Install 7Zip, Java SDK, Eclipse, and MSysGit
2. Use GitHub Web page to fork Twetailer master repository (then you'll have you own copy into your account)
3. Open a command line shell
	3.1 Go to your Eclipse workspace directory: $cd <workspace.dir>
	3.2 Set the JAVA_HOME variable: $set JAVA_HOME=<java.sdk.dir>
	3.3 Launch Git Bash from <workspace.dir> & clone your fork of Twetailer repository: $git clone git@github.com:DomDerrien/twetailerJ.git
	3.4 Keep a local reference of the master respository: $git remote add <your.username> git@/github.com/<your.username>/twetailerJ.git
	3.5 Move to the twetailerJ sub-directory: $cd twetailerJ
	3.6 Create the bin directory: $mkdir bin
	3.7 Unzip the ant program: $<7Zip.dir>\7z.exe x -obin deps\tools\system\apache-ant-1.7.1-bin.zip
	3.8 Unzip the App Engine SDK: $<7Zip.dir>\7z.exe x -obin deps\tools\containers\appengine-java-sdk-1.2.5.zip
	3.9 Run the Ant command: $bin\apache-ant-1.7.1\bin\ant -f build\build-appengine.xml init
	
========================================
Day-to-day development
========================================

1. Open Eclipse to update your files
2. Open a command line shell
	2.1 Set the JAVA_HOME variable: $set JAVA_HOME=<java.sdk.dir>
	2.2 Move to the twetailerJ\build directory: $cd <workspace.dir>\twetailerJ
	2.3 Run the tests with the Ant command: bin\apache-ant-1.7.1\bin\ant -f build\build-appengine.xml test
	2.4 Run the App Engine server with the Ant command: bin\apache-ant-1.7.1\bin\ant -f build\build-appengine.xml webserver-start
	2.5 User the task manager to kill the nested series of JVMs (with the name "java.exe")
3. Run a specific Java test suite
    3.1 Run the tests with the Ant command: bin\apache-ant-1.7.1\bin\ant -f build\build-appengine.xml step-datanucleus-enhance-for-tests step-java-test -Dtestcase=twetailer.validator.TestCommandSettings

========================================
Submit your updates
========================================

1. Open a command line shell
	1.1 Set the JAVA_HOME variable: $set JAVA_HOME=<java.sdk.dir>
	1.2 Move to the twetailerJ directory: $cd <workspace.dir>\twetailerJ
	1.3 Run the Ant command: $build\clean.bat
	1.4 Use Git to submit your patch:
		$git status
		$git add <new.file.path>
		$git commit -a -m "<informative.message.about.the.patch>"
		$git push
	1.5 Or compress the Twetailer files (password-protected) and send the ZIP file to dom.derrien@twetailer.com:
		$<7Zip.dir>\7z.exe a -xr!.git -ptwtlr twetailerJ-patch-<YYYYMMDD.of.the.day>.7z ./*

========================================
Update the application
========================================

1. Copy the files to go on production in a folder like <workspace_dir>/twetailerJ-stage
2. Test the ready-to-deploy code with: bin\apache-ant-1.7.1\bin\ant -f build\build-appengine.xml step-appengine-start
3. Deploy the code with: bin\appengine-java-sdk-1.2.5\bin\appcfg.cmd --email=twetailer@gmail.com update src\war